## 2. Authentication & User Management

### 2.1 Login Page Implementation
**File: `src/pages/LoginPage.jsx`**

**Key Concepts:**
- Form state management with useState
- Password visibility toggle
- Form submission handling
- Loading states during authentication

**Code Analysis:**
```jsx
// File: src/pages/LoginPage.jsx
const LoginPage = () => {
  const [showPassword, setShowPassword] = useState(false);
  const [formData, setFormData] = useState({
    email: "",
    password: "",
  });
  const { login, isLoggingIn } = useAuthStore();

  const handleSubmit = async (e) => {
    e.preventDefault();
    login(formData);
  };

  return (
    <div className="h-screen grid lg:grid-cols-2">
      {/* Form Section */}
      <div className="flex flex-col justify-center items-center p-6 sm:p-12">
        <form onSubmit={handleSubmit} className="space-y-6">
          {/* Email Input */}
          <div className="form-control">
            <input
              type="email"
              value={formData.email}
              onChange={(e) => setFormData({ ...formData, email: e.target.value })}
            />
          </div>
          
          {/* Password Input with Toggle */}
          <div className="relative">
            <input
              type={showPassword ? "text" : "password"}
              value={formData.password}
              onChange={(e) => setFormData({ ...formData, password: e.target.value })}
            />
            <button
              type="button"
              onClick={() => setShowPassword(!showPassword)}
            >
              {showPassword ? <EyeOff /> : <Eye />}
            </button>
          </div>
        </form>
      </div>
      
      {/* Image Pattern Section */}
      <AuthImagePattern title="Welcome back!" />
    </div>
  );
};
```

**Learning Points:**
- **Controlled Components**: Form inputs controlled by React state
- **Object Spread Operator**: `{ ...formData, email: e.target.value }`
- **Conditional Type Attribute**: Toggle between text and password input types
- **Event Prevention**: `e.preventDefault()` prevents default form submission
- **Responsive Grid Layout**: `lg:grid-cols-2` for desktop two-column layout

### 2.2 Sign Up Page Implementation
**File: `src/pages/SignUpPage.jsx`**

**Key Concepts:**
- Client-side form validation
- Custom validation functions
- Toast notifications for user feedback
- Form submission with validation checks

**Code Analysis:**
```jsx
// File: src/pages/SignUpPage.jsx
const SignUpPage = () => {
  const [formData, setFormData] = useState({
    fullName: "",
    email: "",
    password: "",
  });
  const { signup, isSigningUp } = useAuthStore();

  const validateForm = () => {
    if (!formData.fullName.trim()) return toast.error("Full name is required");
    if (!formData.email.trim()) return toast.error("Email is required");
    if (!/\S+@\S+\.\S+/.test(formData.email)) return toast.error("Invalid email format");
    if (!formData.password) return toast.error("Password is required");
    if (formData.password.length < 6) return toast.error("Password must be at least 6 characters");
    return true;
  };

  const handleSubmit = (e) => {
    e.preventDefault();
    const success = validateForm();
    if (success === true) signup(formData);
  };
```

**Learning Points:**
- **Form Validation**: Custom validation function with multiple checks
- **Regular Expressions**: Email format validation using regex pattern
- **String Methods**: `.trim()` to remove whitespace, `.length` for validation
- **Conditional Execution**: Only proceed with signup if validation passes
- **User Feedback**: Toast notifications for validation errors

### 2.3 Profile Page Implementation
**File: `src/pages/ProfilePage.jsx`**

**Key Concepts:**
- File upload handling
- FileReader API for image preview
- Base64 encoding for image upload
- Profile picture update functionality

**Code Analysis:**
```jsx
// File: src/pages/ProfilePage.jsx
const ProfilePage = () => {
  const { authUser, isUpdatingProfile, updateProfile } = useAuthStore();
  const [selectedImg, setSelectedImg] = useState(null);

  const handleImageUpload = async (e) => {
    const file = e.target.files[0];
    if (!file) return;

    const reader = new FileReader();
    reader.readAsDataURL(file);

    reader.onload = async () => {
      const base64Image = reader.result;
      setSelectedImg(base64Image);
      await updateProfile({ profilePic: base64Image });
    };
  };

  return (
    <div className="h-screen pt-20">
      <div className="relative">
        <img
          src={selectedImg || authUser.profilePic || "/avatar.png"}
          alt="Profile"
          className="size-32 rounded-full object-cover border-4"
        />
        <label htmlFor="avatar-upload">
          <Camera className="w-5 h-5 text-base-200" />
          <input
            type="file"
            id="avatar-upload"
            className="hidden"
            accept="image/*"
            onChange={handleImageUpload}
            disabled={isUpdatingProfile}
          />
        </label>
      </div>
    </div>
  );
};
```

**Learning Points:**
- **File Input Handling**: `e.target.files[0]` to get selected file
- **FileReader API**: Converting files to base64 for upload
- **Async/Await**: Handling asynchronous file processing
- **Conditional Image Source**: Fallback chain for profile images
- **Hidden Input Pattern**: Using label to trigger file input
- **Loading States**: Disabling input during upload process

